premise_source_doc_sentence: Virtually any ductile metal may be formed , from aluminum or stainless steel , to high-strength , high-temperature alloys including INX , Inconel , Grade 50 / Corten , and Hastelloy .
In its purest form , it is a bright , slightly reddish yellow , dense , soft , malleable , and ductile metal .
It is a soft , malleable , and ductile metal with very high thermal and electrical conductivity .

In the Roman era , copper was principally mined on Cyprus , the origin of the name of the metal , from aes сyprium  (  metal of Cyprus  )  , later corrupted to сuprum , from which the words copper  (  English  )  , cuivre  (  French  )  , Koper  (  Dutch  )  and Kupfer  (  German  )  are all derived .

It was the first metal to be smelted from its ore , c. 5000 BC , the first metal to be cast into a shape in a mold , c. 4000 BC and the first metal to be purposefully alloyed with another metal , tin , to create bronze , c. 3500 BC .
